.SH "NAME"
Catmandu::Importer::Modules \- list installed perl modules in a given namespace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This Catmandu::Importer list perl modules from all perl library paths with
their \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`version\*(C'\fR, absolute \f(CW\*(C`file\*(C'\fR, library \f(CW\*(C`path\*(C'\fR, and short
description (\f(CW\*(C`about\*(C'\fR).
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
.IX Header "CONFIGURATION"
.IP "file" 4
.IX Item "file"
Read input from a local file given by its path. Alternatively a scalar
reference can be passed to read from a string.
.IP "fh" 4
.IX Item "fh"
Read input from an IO::Handle. If not specified, Catmandu::Util::io is used to
create the input stream from the \f(CW\*(C`file\*(C'\fR argument or by using \s-1STDIN.\s0
.IP "encoding" 4
.IX Item "encoding"
Binmode of the input stream \f(CW\*(C`fh\*(C'\fR. Set to \f(CW\*(C`:utf8\*(C'\fR by default.
.IP "fix" 4
.IX Item "fix"
An \s-1ARRAY\s0 of one or more fixes or file scripts to be applied to imported items.
.IP "namespace" 4
.IX Item "namespace"
Namespace(s) for the modules to list, given as array or comma-separated list
.IP "inc" 4
.IX Item "inc"
List of library paths (defaults to \f(CW@INC\fR)
.IP "max_depth" 4
.IX Item "max_depth"
Maximum depth to recurse into the namespace e.g. if the namespace is
Catmandu::Fix then Catmandu::Fix::add_field has a depth of 1 and
Catmandu::Fix::Condition::exists a depth of 2
.IP "pattern" 4
.IX Item "pattern"
Filter modules by the given regex pattern
.IP "primary" 4
.IX Item "primary"
Filter modules to the first module of each name
.IP "about" 4
.IX Item "about"
Include short description as given in the \s-1NAME\s0 section of each module's
documentation.  Enabled by default.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
Every Catmandu::Importer is a Catmandu::Iterable all its methods are
inherited.
